      "date": "2018-09-26 18:17:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: -Code-Review\n\nOn second thought, I remember that my first implementation was exactly like this one and I've added cl_page allocation later for the reason. As far as I remember at the moment of open there is no cl_object, so lock revocation will not discard pages because of that. I think there is simpler solution - we can update ll_dom_lock_cancel() to call truncate_inode_pages() if lli_clob is NULL",
